        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(opencode): support separate Zen and Go API key env vars",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAllow using both OpenCode GO and OpenCode ZEN with separate environment variables for each catalog, with fallback to the shared `OPENCODE_API_KEY`.\n\nAdd provider-specific OpenCode API key env vars so `opencode` (Zen) and `opencode-go` (Go) can use different credentials instead of being forced to share the same `OPENCODE_API_KEY`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`extensions/opencode/index.ts`**: prefer `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY`, fall back to `OPENCODE_API_KEY`; restore shared profile fan-out so one key configures both catalogs\n- **`extensions/opencode-go/index.ts`**: prefer `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY`, fall back to `OPENCODE_API_KEY`; restore shared profile fan-out\n- **`extensions/opencode/openclaw.plugin.json`**: promote `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` to primary, keep `OPENCODE_API_KEY` as fallback\n- **`extensions/opencode-go/openclaw.plugin.json`**: add `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` as expected env var\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/opencode.ts`**: update to parameterized env var rather than hardcoded `OPENCODE_API_KEY`\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/opencode.test.ts`**: add precedence tests for split-key ordering\n- **`src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts`**: add split-key resolution tests for both providers; add missing `opencode` mock candidate map entry\n- **`docs/providers/opencode.md`** & **`docs/providers/opencode-go.md`**: document the new env vars and precedence order\n\n## Precedence\n\n| Usage | Provider | Prefers | Falls back to |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Zen models | `opencode/...` | `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` | `OPENCODE_API_KEY` |\n| Go models | `opencode-go/...` | `OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY` | `OPENCODE_API_KEY` |\n\n## ClawSweeper P1 Resolution\n\n**Finding**: The original PR removed `profileIds` and `expectedProviders` from the auth method config, breaking users who rely on a single `OPENCODE_API_KEY` for both catalogs. After onboarding Zen, the Go catalog would remain unconfigured.\n\n**Fix**: Restored `OPENCODE_SHARED_PROFILE_IDS = [\"opencode:default\", \"opencode-go:default\"]` in both extensions, plus `profileIds: [...OPENCODE_SHARED_PROFILE_IDS]` and `expectedProviders: [\"opencode\", \"opencode-go\"]` on both auth methods. This means configuring Zen with `OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY` also sets up Go, and vice versa, without losing the split-key preference.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### Behavior or issue addressed\n\nPreviously, both OpenCode Zen (`opencode/...`) and OpenCode Go (`opencode-go/...`) providers shared a single `OPENCODE_API_KEY` environment variable, forcing users with different credentials for each catalog to find workarounds.\n\n### Build verification\n\n- `pnpm build` — passes\n- `pnpm test -- src/plugin-sdk/opencode.test.ts` — 1 test passed\n- `pnpm test -- src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts` — 58 tests passed (with the new split-key tests)\n\n### Real environment tested\n\nOpenClaw local dev environment on macOS (OpenClaw built from PR branch), with separate test API keys for Zen and Go catalogs.\n\n### Exact steps run after this patch\n\n```bash\n# Set split credentials\nexport OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY=*** OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY=*** OPENCODE_API_KEY=*** Verify Zen provider resolves the Zen-specific key\nopenclaw doctor --provider opencode\n# → Resolves OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY ✓\n\n# Verify Go provider resolves the Go-specific key\nopenclaw doctor --provider opencode-go\n# → Resolves OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY ✓\n\n# Verify fallback when Zen-specific key is absent\nunset OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY\nopenclaw doctor --provider opencode\n# → Falls back to OPENCODE_API_KEY ✓\n\n# Verify fallback when Go-specific key is absent\nunset OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY\nopenclaw doctor --provider opencode-go\n# → Falls back to OPENCODE_API_KEY ✓\n```\n\n### What was not tested\n\n- Onboard wizard UI interaction (visual only, no logic change)\n- Remote/cloud deployment with real API keys (local dev only)\n",
        "branch": "feat/opencode-split-provider-keys",
